comments.text:
Was there bit too much smugness (sorry for using this word) @thedeshbhakt, given the issue at hand, which is not fully resolved one way or the other. Just because BJP jumps in to politicise a issue, doesnt diminish the seriousness of the original issue, in case if it has occured. And currently we cant be sure of the truth, especially when additionally there is some amount of misdirection by AAP/Atashi like

a) claiming that cloth is not torn in the partial video clip, when I dont think Maliwal ever mentioned that her cloth was torn, I think she mentioned it was pulled up or so.

b) just saying that one person is rising voice and using strong words, doesnt automatically mean that the other side didnt misbehave before or afterwards.  And it has not been clearly clarified from AAP side that there was no mis behaviour from anyone at their end.

c) Just because Maliwal doesnt appear to explicitly mention assult in the leaked partial video clip, doesnt mean that it might not have occured before and or after this partial clip. Also she does seem to mention about waiting for SHO to arrive or some such thing. If so, it definitly wasnt for chai pe charcha or to inform that the Tea is fantastic.

d) also mounting an attack using a leaked partial mobile video clip, which in reality cant prove things one way or the other in absolute sense, instead of releasing full unedited cctv footages so that people can form their own opinion. 

The way AAP danced around this issue saying one thing sometimes and opposite thing other times. And didnt suspend the person, given the seriousness of the allegations, again coming from a senior person, till enquire is done and truth is found. Also is it that the AAP CM is so special and or busy that he cant show the basic courtesy to meet his own party's MP and long time associate, when they both are at the same place, especially if for what ever reason the MP is insisting that they want to meet him.

Also is AAP suffering from too much mix up of personality cult(s) influenced processes or so ...

As a long time supporter of AAP, the incidents around liquor scam and dancing around it by skipping summons upteen times (even if AAP is fully clean; rather chances are the truth is somewhere in between), then chiefministership, and now this, makes one sad. Also the smuggness and oversmartness of the spokespersons with half truths. No longer sure how they are diffirent from other parties wrt basic ethics and morality, maybe it was expecting too much in the dirty games of politics.
